	<section class=3D"article-content clearfix" itemprop=3D"articleBody">
		<h1>Firewood Stacked Cord Calculator</h1>
<p>We have set up this page to solve a problem. You bought a certain amount=
 of firewood and were told the amount of wood you were paying for and getti=
ng would be the amount normally stated in Cords or partial cords of wood. Y=
ou get the wood delivered, typically dumped in a pile for you to stack. Cal=
culating a random pile to find its volume is well past this site's capabili=
ty. So, to reasonably measure the wood, it needs to be stacked in a cubic d=
imension so it can be calculated using the firewood calculator below. Howev=
er, when you stack the wood, it may not be convenient or possible to do jus=
t one area that fits the standard dimensions of cordwood. Just doing one st=
ack may not work, or multiple cubic piles with different stacked dimensions=
, so you would measure each. Calculate the amount and add them up for the t=
otal.</p>
<p>We have found a calculator that will convert the cubic dimensions of the=
 stack or stacks of wood you have built. Measure what size you have in the =
final stack or stacks. Then, the dimensions of each cube are put together, =
and the blocks are totaled. The calculator will convert the dimensions to a=
 cubic area, and the size is also converted to cubic feet, which is the bas=
is of a cord of firewood (128 cubic feet). You get a cord size calculation =
and a cubic foot calculation.</p>
<p>One of the ways customers use this is when multiple stacks are made it y=
ou do have to do each stack and add the total up. For people like me who ha=
d to take remedial math, this is a lot easier than writing the formula out =
on a spreadsheet. The math goes like this. By definition, cordwood is compa=
ctly stacked firewood, typically stacked 4' wide X 4' high X 8' high. The b=
ottom line in the definition is 128 cubic feet.</p>
<h2>Firewood Calculator: No math required</h2>
<p>So, break down the information into blocks so that you can calculate it =
and find out the quantity of wood you received.</p>
<div id=3D"imgandcalc">
<p><img src=3D"https://bostonfirewood.com/images/firewood-calculator/firewo=
od-calculator_with_boy_4672-v2.jpg" alt=3D"firewood calculator" width=3D"72=
7" height=3D"395" style=3D"margin: 15px 15px 25px 10px; float: left;"></p>
<form id=3D"cordcal">
<div class=3D"input-group"><label for=3D"height">Height:</label> <input nam=
e=3D"height" step=3D"any" type=3D"number" value=3D"0" id=3D"height"><select=
 name=3D"Hunits" id=3D"Hunits"><option value=3D"0">Feet</option><option val=
ue=3D"1">Inches</option><option value=3D"2">Meters</option><option value=3D=
"3">Decimeters</option><option value=3D"4">Centimeters</option></select></d=
iv>
<div class=3D"input-group"><label for=3D"length">Length:</label> <input nam=
e=3D"length2" step=3D"any" type=3D"number" value=3D"0" id=3D"length2"><sele=
ct name=3D"Lunits" id=3D"Lunits"><option value=3D"0">Feet</option><option v=
alue=3D"1">Inches</option><option value=3D"2">Meters</option><option value=
=3D"3">Decimeters</option><option value=3D"4">Centimeters</option></select>=
</div>
<div class=3D"input-group"><label for=3D"depth">Depth:</label> <input name=
=3D"depth" step=3D"any" type=3D"number" value=3D"0" id=3D"depth"><select na=
me=3D"Dunits" id=3D"Dunits"><option value=3D"0">Feet</option><option value=
=3D"1">Inches</option><option value=3D"2">Meters</option><option value=3D"3=
">Decimeters</option><option value=3D"4">Centimeters</option></select></div=
>
<div class=3D"button-group"><button type=3D"button" id=3D"calculate">Calcul=
ate</button> <button type=3D"reset">Clear</button></div>
<p>Cord Output: <span id=3D"cordout">0 cords</span></p>
<p>Imperial Output: <span id=3D"impout">0 cubic feet</span></p>
<p>Metric Output: <span id=3D"metout">0 cubic meters</span></p>
</form></div>
<p>Without being able to verify the quantity you agree to purchase, you jus=
t will not know if it is a fair deal or not.</p>
<p>Here are some reference dimensions.</p>
<p>One cord is 4 X 4 by 8 feet wide =3D 128 cubic feet.</p>
<p>One half of a cord is 16" wide by 4 X 4 high now by 12' long =3D 63.9 cu=
bic feet, so that would be half a cord.</p>
<p>One-third of a cord would be 42.66 cubic feet. It would line ou like one=
 row of 16" pieces. So it calculates this way one row 16" wide 4 feet high =
X 8 feet long =3D 42.66 cubic feet one-third of 128 cubic feet.</p>
<p>These numbers are rounded, but if you extend them out more decimal place=
s, it will come out to the exact number.</p>
<p>So grab the Stanley tape measure and check to see what you get vs. what =
you thought you were getting. Expect some variation based on the tightness =
of stacking, but certainly do not get taken for a ride if it varies a lot b=
etween what you ordered and what you got. If there is a discrepancy, we rec=
ommend contacting the vendor and discussing the situation to see if a reaso=
nable solution can be reached. As in any service/sales business, you would =
want that courtesy if you were the owner. If you are happy with the service=
, let a friend know. If you are not happy with it, contact the company to l=
et them know so they can fix it.</p>
<h3>Firewood Quantities We Sell</h3>
<p>At Bostonfirewood.com, we are geared to be a firewood supplier that does=
 things a little differently. We sell, deliver, and stack kiln-dried firewo=
od for Boston and Metro West customers. We know many customers want;</p>
<ul>
<li>Smaller quantities of wood other than a full cord</li>
<li>Kiln-dried wood delivered</li>
<li>Wood stacked where you want it</li>
<li>Firewood that lights and burns well</li>
<li>A fair measure of wood</li>
<li>We stand behind our firewood product</li>
</ul>
<p>Quantity Options We Provide</p>
<p>Because we sell convenience, we sell firewood in the amounts the custome=
r wants, and we define the amounts here on this site</p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://bostonfirewood.com/our-kiln-dried-firewood/cord-of-w=
ood">Full Cords</a> of kiln-dried firewood</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://bostonfirewood.com/our-kiln-dried-firewood/half-cord=
">Half Cord</a> of kiln-dried firewood delivered and stacked</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://bostonfirewood.com/our-kiln-dried-firewood/face-cord=
">Face Cord</a> or one-third of a cord of kiln-dried firewood delivered and=
 stacked</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://bostonfirewood.com/boston-kiln-dried-firewood/quarte=
r-cord-of-wood" target=3D"_blank">Quarter Cords</a> of kiln-dried firewood<=
/li>
<li><a href=3D"https://bostonfirewood.com/our-kiln-dried-firewood/firewood-=
bundles">Bundles of Kiln dried firewood</a>&nbsp;picked up in our yard</li>
</ul>
<p>To order, call Paul at&nbsp;<a href=3D"tel:781-254-2773">781-254-2773</a=
></p>

